				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If we're making a digital NTSC encoder, I just had an idea for it.<br /><br />A problem with NTSC if having a black pixel surrounded by saturated primary colors is chroma bleeding making the blacks not looking black enough.  So I had the idea of making de-saturated pixels wider by having a fast slope towards greys, but a slower slope towards saturated colors.<br /><br />I made an algorithm for it:<br /><br />a = u^2 + v^2<br />U(n) = u + 2a(U(n-1) - u)<br />V(n) = v + 2a(V(n-1) - v)<br /><br />This might be used in combination with more typical luma/chroma filtering.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
